import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['home_score'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['away_score'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['away_score'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['away_score'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['score_diff'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    plt.hist(data['score_diff'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['score_diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['score_diff'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['score_diff'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['score_diff'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of score differences?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['home_score'], data['away_score'])
    plt.xlabel('Home Score')
    plt.ylabel('Away Score')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between home and away scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    division_count = data.groupby('division')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(division_count['division'], division_count['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of games played by division?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Division')
    plt.ylabel('Count of games played')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
